co occurrence or cooccurrence is a linguistics term that can either mean concurrence coincidence or in a more specific sense the above chance frequent occurrence of two terms from a text corpus alongside each other in a certain order co occurrence in this linguistic sense can be interpreted as an indicator of semantic proximity or an idiomatic expression in contrast to collocation co occurrence assumes interdependency of the two terms a co occurrence restriction is identified when linguistic elements never occur together analysis of these restrictions can lead to discoveries about the structure and development of a language 1 edit see also linguistics portal correlation distributional hypothesis statistical semantics co occurrence matrix co occurrence networks edit references kroeger paul 2005 analyzing grammar an introduction cambridge cambridge university press pp 160 20 isbn 160 978 0 521 01653 7 this linguistics article is a stub you can help wikipedia by expanding it v t e 